cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the backhaul challenge in heterogeneous wireless networks and proposes a hybrid caching and multicasting design to support content delivery. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper deals with the successful transmission probability and optimization of design parameters. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper considers the joint optimization of caching and multicasting in a large-scale system. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper aims to support massive content delivery in heterogeneous wireless networks. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses optimization techniques to solve a mixed discrete-continuous optimization problem.
